# Vue Code Quality

**MANDATORY** when writing or modifying any `.vue` file or app `.ts` file:

1. Use **TypeScript** with explicit types; avoid JSDoc for types when TypeScript is available
2. Use **Vue 3** and **`<script setup>`** only; no Options API unless migrating legacy code
3. Follow **post-edit verification**: run typecheck, lint, and format (see post-edit-verification rule) and fix all reported issues before finishing
4. When unsure about Vue or Nuxt best practices or APIs, **if your client exposes Nuxt documentation MCP tools**, use them to browse the official guides; otherwise use local inspection and the [Nuxt documentation](https://nuxt.com/docs).

Rely on **@nuxt/eslint** (Vue + Nuxt rules); fix all ESLint issues before considering the task complete.
